Remediation recommendations
1. Patch / replace Icecast 2.0.4 — end of life software.
2. Enable LSASS protection (RunAsPPL) to prevent credential dumping.
3. Restrict outbound connections from media server.
4. Deploy EDR — process injection and log clearing would have triggered alerts.
5. Audit scheduled tasks and run keys weekly.
Lessons learned
Unpatched legacy software exploitable with a 20-year-old CVE. SeImpersonatePrivilege enabled by default — common misconfiguration that enabled trivial PrivEsc.
